biography: [Florian Bruhin](https://bruhin.software/) ("The Compiler") is a long-time contributor and maintainer of both the [pytest](https://www.pytest.org/) framework and various plugins. In 2013, he started the [qutebrowser](https://www.qutebrowser.org) project, a keyboard-focused web browser based on Python and Qt. In 2015, he discovered pytest - since then, he has given talks and conducted workshops about pytest at various conferences and companies.
